# Competitive moat analysis reveals three durable sources of advantage
@type: comparison

@compare:
  header: Moat Source | Strength | Evidence | Durability
  row: Proprietary data asset | Strong | 7-year transaction database with 400M+ data points | High — cannot be replicated quickly
  row: Integration ecosystem | Strong | 140+ native integrations vs. competitor average of 28 | High — creates switching cost
  row: Domain expertise in FSI | Moderate | 60% of R&D focused on FSI-specific features | Medium — replicable with investment
  row: Brand and community | Moderate | NPS 64, active user community of 45K members | Medium — built over time

@exhibit: Exhibit 2 — Competitive Moat Assessment
@source: McKinsey competitive analysis; customer interviews N=42; competitor product teardowns, 2024

@notes: The integration ecosystem is the most defensible moat. With 140 integrations, switching cost is not just financial — it is operational. Customers embed NovaTech into their workflows.

