# Three risks require management attention but do not break the deal thesis
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Risk 1: Competitive Intensification (Medium)
  - Salesforce announced adjacent product in Q2 2024
  - However: Salesforce historically struggles with vertical depth
  - Mitigation: accelerate FSI and healthcare vertical investment
  - Timeline: competitive response needed within 12 months

@col:
  ## Risk 2: Key Talent Retention (Medium-High)
  - 4 of 6 founding engineers are not under long-term contracts
  - Median tenure of engineering team: 2.1 years (low)
  - Mitigation: retention packages at close ($28M budget)
  - Timeline: retention agreements before close announcement

@notes: Risk 2 is the most time-sensitive. Engineering departures in the 90 days post-announcement are the single largest destroyer of value in software acquisitions.

